      • interpretFields

        protected java.util.Collection interpretFields()
                                        throws SAFSException
        Calls the default processing of interpretFields and then prepares the droiddata (testRecordData) with the initial KeywordProperties of:

          KEY_COMMAND=non-null
          KEY_PARAM_1-N (param1 - paramN, even if > 9)

        Keyword implementations will need to add to these properties:

          KEY_TARGET
          KEY_PARAM_TIMEOUT (may be different for each keyword)
        Overrides:
        interpretFields in class DriverCommand
        Returns:
        Collection of the parameter(s)
        Throws:
        SAFSException

      • process

        public void process()
        Description copied from class: Processor
        The primary method that all subclasses must implement. The implementation here simply checks for any chainedProcessor,
        invokes chainedProcessor.setParams(this.getParams()),
        invokes chainedProcessor.process(),
        invokes setRecordProcessed(chainedProcessor.isRecordProcessed()).

        Thus, any subclassing Processor should attempt to process it's own commands and then invoke super.process() to try any chained Processor(s).

        Otherwise, by default executes setRecordProcessed(false) if no chainedProcessor is present.

        Overrides:
        process in class Processor

      • processProperties

        protected void processProperties(int param_timeout)
                          throws java.lang.IllegalThreadStateException,
                                 RemoteException,
                                 java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException,
                                 ShutdownInvocationException
        Sets Property PARAM_TIMEOUT and then processes the completed remote control action properties. This method is called internally by individual keyword implementations. After returning from remote processing the routine updates the droiddata via DUtilities.captureRemoteResultsProperties(RemoteResults, DTestRecordHelper). This routine then calls processResults(RemoteResults).
        Throws:
        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException - if the Ready, Running, or Results signals timeout.
        java.lang.IllegalThreadStateException - if sockets communications failed.
        ShutdownInvocationException - if sockets communication signals a shutdown has commenced.
        RemoteException - if the remote client has issued an Exception.
        See Also:
        DUtilities.captureRemoteResultsProperties(RemoteResults, DTestRecordHelper)

      • processResourceMessageInfoResults

        protected boolean processResourceMessageInfoResults(int msgType)
        Logs any message or message with detail that might be captured in the current droiddata. The routine does not set or change any statusCode or statusInfo information.

        If a message was found and logged, the routine returns TRUE. This means the caller does NOT have to log any success or failure message.

        If no message was found, then the routine will return FALSE and the caller will need to log an appropriate message.

        Parameters:
        msgType - -- int message type identifier constant as defined in AbstractLogFacility.
        Returns:
        true if we did find and handle a ResoureMessageInfo result. false otherwise.

      • logResourceMessageFailure

        protected void logResourceMessageFailure()
        Log a FAILED_MESSAGE using whatever ResourceMessageInfo data is returned in droiddata. The command does not change any statusCode or statusInfo information. Calls processResourceMessageInfoResults(int) to attempt the logging. If there was no ResourceMessageInfo, we still log a generic failed message via Processor.issueActionFailure(String).

      • doGUIBranching

        protected void doGUIBranching()
                       throws java.lang.IllegalThreadStateException,
                              RemoteException,
                              java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException,
                              ShutdownInvocationException
        OnGuiExistsGotoBlockID and OnGuiNotExistGotoBlockID commands setup.

        Validates the presence of:
        BLOCKID (PARAM_1)
        WINDOWID (PARAM_2 and KEY_WINNAME)
        COMPID (PARAM_3 and KEY_COMPNAME)
        and the optional TIMEOUT parameter (PARAM_4 && PARAM_TIMEOUT)

        Through DUtilities.getAppMapRecognition(DTestRecordHelper) adds:
        KEY_WINREC
        KEY_COMPREC

        The current implementation does expect recognition strings to exist in the App Map. If none are found, the command will issue a failure without making a remote call.

        Upon successful execution of the command, the remote process should return:

          StatusCode = NO_SCRIPT_FAILURE (condition met) allow the branching to occur.
          StatusCode = SCRIPT_WARNING (condition not met) but no failures occurred -- do not branch.
          StatusCode = anything else will expect RemoteMessageInfo(s) to report the failure.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalThreadStateException
        RemoteException
        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException
        ShutdownInvocationException

      • doClipboardCommand

        protected void doClipboardCommand()
                           throws java.lang.IllegalThreadStateException,
                                  RemoteException,
                                  java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException,
                                  ShutdownInvocationException
        Process clipboard related keywords:
        AssignClipboardVariable
        ClearClipboard
        SaveClipboardToFile
        SetClipboard
        VerifyClipboardToFile

        Validates the presence of:
        FileName (PARAM_1) for keyword SaveClipboardToFile and VerifyClipboardToFile
        ContentToSet (PARAM_1) for keyword SetClipboard
        VariableName (PARAM_1) for keyword AssignClipboardVariable

        Then pass the command to the remote side to be processed.

        Upon successful execution of the command, the remote process should return:

          StatusCode = NO_SCRIPT_FAILURE -- condition met in timeout period.
          StatusCode = anything else will expect RemoteMessageInfo(s) to report the failure.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalThreadStateException
        RemoteException
        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException
        ShutdownInvocationException

      • doTakeScreenShotResults

        protected void doTakeScreenShotResults(RemoteResults results)
        Process result of keyword TakeScreenShot.
        The remote device side will return the rotate degree of the device.
        The ScreenShot will be got through API of the AndroidDebugBridger at computer side.
        The returned image is always that you put your device at the default direction.
        We should rotate that returned image back if the tested android application is rotatable.
        Parameters:
        results - RemoteResults, returned from the processProperties call.

      • doClipboardResults

        protected void doClipboardResults(RemoteResults results)
        Process result of clipboard related keywords:
        AssignClipboardVariable
        ClearClipboard
        SaveClipboardToFile
        SetClipboard
        VerifyClipboardToFile

        Upon successful execution of the command, the remote process should return:

          StatusCode = NO_SCRIPT_FAILURE -- remote execution succeed. We need continue process at local side.
          StatusCode = anything else will expect RemoteMessageInfo(s) to report the failure.

        Parameters:
        results - -- returned from the processProperties call.
